com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.chart.definitions

Class AbstractChartDefinition<T extends AbstractDimension,D extends ChartData>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.chart.definitions.AbstractChartDefinition<T,D>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    HeatmapDefinition, LineChartDefinition, PieChartDefinition

    public abstract class AbstractChartDefinition<T extends AbstractDimension,D extends ChartData>
extends java.lang.Object
    Generic definition of a chart. Base definition that every specific chart definition must extend.

    Charts must at least have a name and a DataSource.

    Dimensions specify the data to extract for visualization. This is based on the type of the chart.

    Filters provide the ability to filter data out based on criteria specified in the definition or per request. Operations provide the ability to do data optimization. Optimization is based on grouping and aggregation. Filters and Operations are optional. When they are not defined that data will not be optimized in any way.

    A ChartPostProcessor can be defined to do further optimation of the data after it is generated by the framework.

    Author:
    Philipp Schürmann
